text.tspan: Per capita methane emissions from agriculture
Methane (CH₄) emissions are measured in tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalents (CO₂e), based on 100-year global
warming potential factors for non-CO₂ gases.
Source: Our World in Data based on Climate Analysis Indicators Tool (CAIT).
